## Technical Notes

**JetBrains**: Does NOT support direct HTTP MCP — uses `npx mcp-remote` as a local stdio→HTTP bridge. Node 20+ required. Config via UI (Settings > Tools > AI Assistant > MCP) or `.jb-mcp.json`.

**Windsurf**: Native Streamable HTTP support. Config: `~/.codeium/windsurf/mcp_config.json` with `serverUrl` field.

**Gemini CLI**: Native HTTP support via `httpUrl` field in `~/.gemini/settings.json` or `.gemini/settings.json`.

**Codex**: Both methods already documented in codex.mdx. Option A: `codex mcp add civic --transport http https://app.civic.com/hub/mcp`. Option B: Settings → MCP Servers → Add Server → Streamable HTTP → paste CIVIC_URL and CIVIC_TOKEN. Just needs Hub Bridge demoted to legacy.

**Anthropic SDK**: MCP still in public beta. Current header: `anthropic-beta: mcp-client-2025-11-20`. Header still required as of early 2026.

**LangChain/LangGraph**: Uses `langchain-mcp-adapters` package, `MultiServerMCPClient` with `streamable_http` transport. Env vars: `CIVIC_URL` (full URL with params), `CIVIC_TOKEN`. Reference impl: github.com/titus-civic/langchain-nexus-reference-implementation.

